Windows System Engineer
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/04/30 08:59:09
Ref. JB3045748
Job Description
Windows system engineer is responsible for managing and supporting Windows servers from the University data center and in distributed locations.
Duties and Responsibilities:
• Solves server-related problems on a daily basis.
• In support of change management within the data center, provides the CSC with information about the enterprise Windows systems.
• Daily verifies all enterprise Windows Systems by using the monitoring tools and proactively intervenes to solve problems or acknowledge the problem to the senior engineer to work together to solve the problem.
• Responsible of monitoring all windows servers and services.
• Management and updating of all enterprise services running on Windows platforms.
• Responsible for Windows account delegation.
• Co-ordinates work with vendors for support.
• Tests and deploys new enterprise servers and services.
• Knowledge of IT Service Management frameworks.
• Design and execute VBScript, PowerShell scripts to automate bulk tasks.
• Performing standard administration responsibilities
• Maintains accurate and comprehensive documentation diagrams of the enterprise servers and backup infrastructure and communications flow and routing.
• Perform pro-active support functions and reporting to maintain the integrity of the enterprise equipment and infrastructure.
• Other duties as assigned.
Skills
• Good Knowledge of MS Active Directory required.
• Expert Knowledge of Windows 2003, 2008, 2012 administration.
• Good practical experience with Server Virtualization.
• Knowledge of server hardware components, how to do diagnostics and how to replace them.
• Good communication skills & Report Writing Skills.
• Must be able to work under pressure in a fast-paced work environment.
• Must be able to work flexible hours including evenings, weekends, holidays and overtime as required, should be available 24/7 on-call in case of major services outage.
• Experience creating simple to complex scripted solutions for various tasks (Powershell, VbScripting, etc.)
• Strong problem solving, testing, and network troubleshooting skills.
• MCITP qualification would be beneficiary.
• 3 years’ experience in server administration.
Education
Bachelor degree required in Computer Engineering/Science
